sentences: Arnold George Dorsey  (born 2 May 1936), known professionally as Engelbert Humperdinck, is a British pop singer who has been described as "one of the finest middle-of-the-road balladeers around".
He achieved international prominence in 1967 with the hit single "Release Me".
Humperdinck's recordings of "Release Me" and "The Last Waltz" both topped the UK Singles Chart in 1967, selling more than a million copies each.
During the 1970s, he had North American chart successes with "After the Lovin'" (1976) and "This Moment in Time" (1979).
